---
name: mcp-client-invoke
requires: Feature.McpClient
---

# MCP client — callTool round-trip

Spawns `mcp-server-tools.ssc` as a subprocess, calls `echo` and `add`
tools, asserts expected output.
Skipped on backends without `Feature.McpClient`.

Note: requires `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` and the server script compiled.

```scalascript
[mcpConnect, Transport](std/mcp/client.ssc)

val client = mcpConnect(Transport.Spawn("node", List("examples/mcp-server-tools.js")))

// List tools
val tools = client.listTools()
println(tools.size >= 3)

// callTool — echo
val echoResult = client.callTool("echo", Map("message" -> "hello"))
println(echoResult.isError)
println(echoResult.content.head match { case c if c.toString.contains("hello") => "ok"; case _ => "fail" })

// callTool — add
val addResult = client.callTool("add", Map("a" -> 3.0, "b" -> 4.0))
println(addResult.isError)
println(addResult.content.head match { case c if c.toString.contains("7") => "ok"; case _ => "fail" })

client.close()
println(client.isClosed)
```
